## 1. Security ke Basic Concepts

### 1.1 Pehchaan (Identity)
Identity ka matlab hai kisi user ya system ka asli hona. Jab hum kisi system me login karte hain, hum apni pehchaan batate hain.

**Example:** Username aur password use karke email account open karna.

---

### 1.2 Raazdari (Confidentiality)
Iska matlab hai ki information sirf usi insaan tak pahuchni chahiye jisko uska access mila ho.

**Example:** WhatsApp ka end-to-end encryption—sirf sender aur receiver message padh sakte hain.

---

### 1.3 Data ki Sudhta (Integrity)
Data waisa ka waisa hi hona chahiye jaisa originally tha—beech mein koi badlav nahi hona chahiye.

**Example:** File download ke baad uska hash verify karna (jaise SHA-256) taake confirm ho ki file change nahi hui.

---

## 2. Role-Based Access Control (RBAC)

RBAC ka matlab hai ki users ko unke kaam ke hisaab se access diya jata hai. Har role ke apne rules aur permissions hote hain.

**Example:** Bank me manager ko full account access hota hai, par cashier sirf cash entry dekh sakta hai.

**Fayde:**
- Easy permission management  
- Kam galti ka chance  
- Secure aur organized system

---

## 3. Single Sign-On (SSO)

SSO ek technique hai jisme user sirf ek baar login karta hai aur fir multiple apps ya websites ko bina dobara login kiye access kar sakta hai.

**Example:** Google account se login karne par Gmail, YouTube, Drive sab chal jata hai.

**Fayde:**
- Time bachta hai  
- Password bhoolne ka chance kam  
- Centralized security control

---

## 4. Proxy Servers aur Firewalls

### Proxy Server
Proxy ek beech ka server hota hai jo user aur internet ke beech ka kaam karta hai. Ye user ki identity chhupata hai, ya access ko control karta hai.

**Example:** School me proxy use hota hai taake students gaming sites na kholen.

### Firewall
Firewall ek security tool hai jo decide karta hai ki kaunsa network traffic allow hoga aur kaunsa block hoga.

**Example:** Company ka firewall har unknown IP address ko block kar deta hai.

---

## 5. Real-life Security Incidents

### Target Data Breach (2013)
Hackers ne ek third-party vendor ke through Target company ke servers ko hack kiya. 40 million se zyada logon ka credit card data chori hua.

**Seekh:** Third-party access par control hona chahiye.

---

### Equifax Breach (2017)
Ek software me vulnerability chhodi gayi thi jo patch nahi hui. Hackers ne 147 million logon ka data chura liya.

**Seekh:** Regular software updates aur patching zaroori hai.

---

### SolarWinds Attack (2020)
Attackers ne trusted software update me malware daal diya jisse thousands companies effect hui.

**Seekh:** Software updates bhi verify karne chahiye. Zero Trust model adopt karna chahiye.

---

